Package: MRplus
Title: Visualising Robustness of Mendelian Randomization Results
Version: 1.0.1
Authors@R: 
    person("Jiahan", "Zhao", , "Loaffff@icloud.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides a set of visualization tools for assessing the robustness 
    of Mendelian randomization (MR) results. The package implements three core 
    functions: (1) inspecting how linkage disequilibrium (LD) pruning parameters 
    affect the number of selected instruments; (2) comparing MR estimates across 
    multiple instrument selection thresholds; and (3) summarising the robustness 
    of multi-exposure and multi-outcome MR analyses using bubble plots. These 
    functions facilitate sensitivity checks, robustness evaluation, and detection 
    of potential publication bias in MR studies.
